  "texts": [
    "The latest PR-targeted work Zhang et al. (2025), though aimed at PR, is not based on the perturbation risk function in Def. 2.",
    "Instead, it is closer to the traditional AT formulation in Eq. 3, introducing a new min-max objective designed to identify AEs that lie in the largest all-AE region k (i.e., PR(x + δ, k) = 0).",
    "They achieve this by designing a numerical algorithm that first uses PGD to generate a diverse set of AEs at different local optima, i.e., S = {x ′ 1, x ′ 2,.",
    "For each x ′ i, gradient descent is then performed toward the nearest decision boundary, and the AE with the largest distance to its nearest boundary is selected, corresponding to the largest all-AE region.",
    "Formally, for a model f θ trained on dataset D, the objective of AT-PR is:"
  ]
}